In addition we are a happy and supportive community of pupils, staff and parents in which learning in its widest sense flourishes. We prepare girls to take advantage of all the opportunities which life offers them, fostering a sense of pleasure, and enjoyment in everything they do, while learning to understand and contribute to the wider community.\r\n\r\nIf you are a prospective parent the best way to catch the spirit of this delightful school is to come and visit us.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to meeting you.\r\n\r\nMs Lucinda Hunt  BSc, ARCS, London\r\nHead\r\n\r\n</div>','Head\'s Welcome','','inherit','open','open','','36-revision-2','','','2013-06-11 04:36:02','2013-06-11 04:36:02','',36,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=214',0,'revision','',0),(215,1,'2013-06-18 11:06:53','2013-06-18 11:06:53','<div id=\"cm_ctl00_FeatureWebpartZone1_ctl00_BodyContent\">\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"color: #e2284d; font-family: Verdana;\"> From the Principal’s Desk……</span></p>\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">As we reflect on the past years, we feel overwhelmed by God’s Grace that has been upon our School. How wonderfully God has led us and how faithful He has been. “His Faithfulness endures forever”, says the Bible and we have truly experienced this in our journey thus far. We thank God for enabling Mount Carmelites to excel in various fields. </span></p>\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">The selection of our Robotics Team to participate in the World Robot Olympiad at Manila, Philippines, was another feather in the cap. However we cannot be complacent looking at the achievements that we have made, we must continue to strive harder with all diligence. With so much of corruption and evil around us, where more and more people are trying to achieve their selfish goals by perverse means, Mount Carmelites you need to be careful and never ever fall into evil devices of the devil.</span></p>\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">“There is a path that seems right to a man, but the end of it is destruction”, says the Bible. So choose the right path to tread upon and the end result would be blessings. In making the right choice you should not depend upon your own capabilities and understanding. “Trust in the Lord with all your heart and lean not to your own understanding, in all your ways acknowledge Him and He shall direct your path.”</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #e2284d;\">God Bless you!\nDr. Earnest Charles J. Samuel </span>\n\n</div>','Head\'s Welcome','','inherit','open','open','','36-autosave','','','2013-06-18 11:06:53','2013-06-18 11:06:53','',36,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=215',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2013-06-19 03:48:13','2013-06-19 03:48:13','<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"color: #e2284d; font-family: Verdana;\"> From the Vice Principal’s Desk……</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Mount Carmelites delight yourself in the Lord and He shall give you the desires of your heart. Pray without ceasing. You don’t have to be on your knees always praying frantically for God to hear you. Prayer is something you can and should be doing all the time, no matter whatever you are doing. Ask wisdom from God and He will give it to you. </span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Start and end your day with a quiet time with God. Begin your quiet time by putting your problems and concerns in God’s capable and loving hands. Prayer is the most powerful form of energy that one can generate. The influence of prayer in human mind and body is as demonstrate as that of glands in our body which secretes hormones. The result can be measured in terms of greater intellectual vigor, moral stamina and a deeper understanding of human relationships. Prayer is nothing but the two way communication with God. </span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">God can help you solve every problem, answer your every question, heal all your heart aches, comfort you when you are sorrowful, give you joy and peace of mind. Be anxious for nothing but in everything by prayer and supplication, with thanks giving, let your request be made known to God. Prayer draws on the power of God, so you will be able to accomplish more and do so more easily. Those who wait on the Lord shall renew their strength. You do your part to the fullest of your capability and allow God to do the rest.\r\n\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #e2284d;\">God Bless you!\r\nDr. Annie Charles Samuel</span></span></p>','Vice Principal','','publish','open','open','','vice-principal','','','2013-06-19 03:48:13','2013-06-19 03:48:13','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=216',0,'page','',0),(217,1,'2013-06-19 03:47:42','2013-06-19 03:47:42','','From the Vice Principal’s Desk……','','inherit','open','open','','216-revision','','','2013-06-19 03:47:42','2013-06-19 03:47:42','',216,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=217',0,'revision','',0),(218,1,'2013-06-19 03:49:14','2013-06-19 03:49:14','<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"color: #e2284d; font-family: Verdana;\"> From the Vice Principal’s Desk……</span></p>\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Mount Carmelites delight yourself in the Lord and He shall give you the desires of your heart. Pray without ceasing. You don’t have to be on your knees always praying frantically for God to hear you. Prayer is something you can and should be doing all the time, no matter whatever you are doing. Ask wisdom from God and He will give it to you. </span></p>\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Start and end your day with a quiet time with God. Begin your quiet time by putting your problems and concerns in God’s capable and loving hands. Prayer is the most powerful form of energy that one can generate. The influence of prayer in human mind and body is as demonstrate as that of glands in our body which secretes hormones. The result can be measured in ter