rdpress/?p=239',0,'revision','',0),(240,1,'2013-06-19 05:19:26','2013-06-19 05:19:26',' ','','','publish','open','open','','240','','','2013-06-25 10:49:17','2013-06-25 10:49:17','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=240',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(241,1,'2013-06-19 05:19:27','2013-06-19 05:19:27',' ','','','publish','open','open','','241','','','2013-06-25 10:49:18','2013-06-25 10:49:18','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=241',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(242,1,'2013-06-19 05:19:27','2013-06-19 05:19:27',' ','','','publish','open','open','','242','','','2013-06-25 10:49:18','2013-06-25 10:49:18','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=242',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(243,1,'2013-06-19 05:19:27','2013-06-19 05:19:27',' ','','','publish','open','open','','243','','','2013-06-25 10:49:18','2013-06-25 10:49:18','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=243',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(244,1,'2013-06-14 11:37:53','2013-06-14 11:37:53','','Gallery','','inherit','open','open','','82-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 11:37:53','2013-06-14 11:37:53','',82,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=244',0,'revision','',0),(245,1,'2013-06-18 06:11:26','2013-06-18 06:11:26','<center><div style=\"width: 140px; height: 30px; background-color: #800000;\">\r\n<h4 style=\"color: #ffffff; text-align: center;\">Apply Online</h4>\r\n</div></center>\r\n\r\n<hr style=\"color: #fff; border-left: 1px none #000000; border-right: 1px none #000000; border-top: 1px none #000000; border-bottom: 1px dotted #000000; background-color: #fff;\" align=\"left\" />\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admissions to all the classes are ordinarily made in December and January for the academic year starting in April. However children are registered for all classes from November.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admissions are made on the basis of merit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students coming from other schools should produce: -\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The leaving/transfer certificate from the school last attended / bonafide certificate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The progress report of his/her academic performance and co-curricular activities in      that  school.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The original birth certificate &amp; a copy of the same.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>A calendar month’s notice in writing should be given by the parents before withdrawing a student from the school. Failure to do so will entail paying fees for the entire term.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students leaving school after December will pay fees for January, February and March also.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">All dues to the school should be paid before applying for transfer certificate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The transfer and other school certificates will be applied for in writing, one week in advance.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The refund of caution money will be made only at the end of the session, on due notice.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Principal can at any time in the interest of the school have a student removed, if in the Pricipal\'s sole discretion, the student or his/her parents/guardian fail to abide by the rules and regulations and in case there is lack of co-operation on the part of the parent in maintaining discipline of the school and his/her continued presence is deterimental to the interest of the other students.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #800000; font-size: 20px;\">Examination &amp; Promotion</span></h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Continuous &amp; Comprehensive Evaluation (C.C.E) introduced by the CBSE, Delhi, which is a system of School Based Assessment that covers all aspects of the student\'s development, is followed in the school. C.C.E covers both the scholastic and co-scholastic aspects of school education.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The school academic year has two terms, April to Sep. and Oct. to March. There will be a Summative assessment for classes VI to X at the end of each term. Besides these there will be two unit tests in each subject as a part of the two Formative assessments, in each term. However there will be no such summative assessments for classes Pre-Nursery to V and only two two evaluations (details would be given along with the syllabus) will be conducted for the students of class I to V. Progress cards will be issued to the students only at the end of the session.\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 100px;\">Assessments (classes VI to X)\r\nUnit tests : 20 marks\r\nOther Assessments, Project work etc. :30 marks\r\nSummative Assessements(classes VI to X) :100 marks</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Assessments/Unit Tests will neither be anticipated nor postponed. Any tampering with marks will be seriously dealt with. Students who are ill should not be sent to appear for Assessments/Unit Tests. Their results can be decided on the basis of their performance in class. However a medical certificate will have to be produced in such cases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students found using any unfair means during Assessments/Unit Tests will be marked zero in that subject. No re-test will be held for such students and they will not be eligible for any academic award or school appointment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Criteria for the award of a Scholar Badge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>VI-VIII : Grade A1 (Marks range 91-100) Eng, Hindi, Maths, S. Science, Gen. Science.\r\nIX: Grade A1 (Marks range 91-100) Eng, IInd Lang., Maths, S. Science, Gen. Science</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The final result will be decided according to the average marks obtained in two terms.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Results declared at the close of the year are final and will not be reconsidered.</li>\r\n</ul>','Admissions','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-38','','','2013-06-18 06:11:26','2013-06-18 06:11:26','',8,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=245',0,'revision','',0),(246,1,'2013-06-19 09:41:17','2013-06-19 09:41:17','[gallery id=\"248\"]','Facilities','','inherit','open','open','','74-autosave','','','2013-06-19 09:41:17','2013-06-19 09:41:17','',74,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=246',0,'revision','',0),(247,1,'2013-06-19 07:42:51','2013-06-19 07:42:51','<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC41931-150x150.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-91\" alt=\"SFC41931-150x150\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC41931-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> <a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC_63522-150x150.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-94\" alt=\"SFC_63522-150x150\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC_63522-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> <a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC_0623-150x150.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-92\" alt=\"SFC_0623-150x150\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC_0623-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> <a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC_9345-150x150.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-93\" alt=\"SFC_9345-150x150\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC_9345-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> <a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC1548-150x150.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-88\" alt=\"SFC1548-150x150\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SFC1548-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>','gallery 2','','inherit','open','open','','98-autosave','','','2013-06-19 07:42:51','2013-06-19 07:42:51','',98,'http://loc