pal’s Desk……</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">As we reflect on the past years, we feel overwhelmed by God’s Grace that has been upon our School. How wonderfully God has led us and how faithful He has been. “His Faithfulness endures forever”, says the Bible and we have truly experienced this in our journey thus far. We thank God for enabling Mount Carmelites to excel in various fields. </span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">The selection of our Robotics Team to participate in the World Robot Olympiad at Manila, Philippines, was another feather in the cap. However we cannot be complacent looking at the achievements that we have made, we must continue to strive harder with all diligence. With so much of corruption and evil around us, where more and more people are trying to achieve their selfish goals by perverse means, Mount Carmelites you need to be careful and never ever fall into evil devices of the devil.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">“There is a path that seems right to a man, but the end of it is destruction”, says the Bible. So choose the right path to tread upon and the end result would be blessings. In making the right choice you should not depend upon your own capabilities and understanding. “Trust in the Lord with all your heart and lean not to your own understanding, in all your ways acknowledge Him and He shall direct your path.”\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #e2284d;\">God Bless you!\r\nDr. Earnest Charles J. Samuel </span></span></div>','Head\'s Welcome','','inherit','open','open','','36-revision-3','','','2013-06-18 11:05:52','2013-06-18 11:05:52','',36,'http://localhost/wordpress/36-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(333,1,'2013-06-22 09:48:53','2013-06-22 09:48:53','','Home Work','','publish','open','open','','home-work','','','2013-06-23 08:30:12','2013-06-23 08:30:12','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=333',0,'page','',0),(334,1,'2013-06-22 09:48:29','2013-06-22 09:48:29','','Home Work','','inherit','open','open','','333-revision','','','2013-06-22 09:48:29','2013-06-22 09:48:29','',333,'http://localhost/wordpress/333-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(335,1,'2013-06-22 09:48:53','2013-06-22 09:48:53','','Home Work','','inherit','open','open','','333-revision-2','','','2013-06-22 09:48:53','2013-06-22 09:48:53','',333,'http://localhost/wordpress/333-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(336,1,'2013-06-23 07:46:33','2013-06-23 07:46:33','','Home Work','','inherit','open','open','','333-revision-3','','','2013-06-23 07:46:33','2013-06-23 07:46:33','',333,'http://localhost/wordpress/333-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(337,1,'2013-06-25 04:42:12','2013-06-25 04:42:12','','founders','','inherit','open','open','','founders-2','','','2013-06-25 04:42:12','2013-06-25 04:42:12','',21,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/founders1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(338,1,'2013-06-21 10:22:07','2013-06-21 10:22:07','<h4>About Mount Carmel School</h4>\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" />\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Mount Carmel School is a Senior Secondary School being run under the aegis of Mount Carmel Educational Society, Chandigarh (Regd.), a group of Christian teachers, dedicated to the cause of complete moral, intellectual and social development of boys and girls. We derive our inspiration from the Lord Jesus Christ who loves children and we fully believe in the commandment given by Him, \'Love thy neighbour as thyself\'. On this, the motto of our school ‘Amor Vincit Omnia\' is based.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/founders.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-105\" alt=\"founders\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/founders-161x300.jpg\" width=\"161\" height=\"300\" /></a>Mount Carmel School was founded by Dr. Earnest Charles J. Samuel &amp; Dr. Annie Charles Samuel in April 1987.\r\n</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"justify\">At present it has a strength of around 2200 students on rolls, in classes Pre-Nursery to XII. The school is Recognized by the Department of Education U.T., Chandigarh and is Affiliated to the Central Board of Secondary Education (C.B.S.E.), Delhi.</p>\r\nThe school has well qualified, experienced and dedicated teachers and boasts of excellent results in the All India Secondary School Examination conducted by the C.B.S.E. Besides laying emphasis on Academic Excellence, the students are encouraged to participate in various co-curricular &amp; extra-curricular activities in the field of performing Arts, Martial arts, FIne arts, Theatre etc.\r\n<div id=\"about_link\"><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/information/\" target=\"_blank\"> <b>Comprehensive Information</b></a></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Various competitions and contests viz., Quiz, Recitation, Story telling, Calligraphy, Reading, Debate/Declamation, Dumb Charades, Essay/Short story writing, Drawing, Painting &amp; Singing etc., are held regularly, which help in the all round development of the students.</p>\r\n\r\nThe school also lays emphasis on sports and games for the physical development of boys and girls. At present, the school extends Facilities for Basketball, Football, Cricket, Lawn Tennis, Net Ball, , Carrom, Chess, Kho-Kho, Karate, Gymnastics, Roller Skating, Sepak Takraw, Athletics etc. Computer education is imparted to students from class II onwards.\r\n\r\nThe school is situated in serene surroundings in a plot of around 3 acres, in sector 47 B, Chandigarh, the city beautiful situated at the foothills of the Shivalik Mountains a part of the Himalayas.\r\n\r\nExcellent Hostel facility is available for students of classes I to XII, where students are provided with cozy comforts of a home away from home, with all modern amenities. (only 40 seats). For further details, contact school reception from 8.00 am to 4.00 pm on any working day. Tel: 0172-2630145 , 6532783\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-51','','','2013-06-21 10:22:07','2013-06-21 10:22:07','',21,'http://localhost/wordpress/21-revision-51/',0,'revision','',0),(339,1,'2013-06-25 06:12:33','2013-06-25 06:12:33','test','test','','trash','closed','closed','','test','','','2013-06-25 07:20:53','2013-06-25 07:20:53','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=339',0,'tribe_events','',0),(340,1,'2013-06-25 06:13:35','2013-06-25 06:13:35','test','test','','inherit','open','open','','339-autosave','','','2013-06-25 06:13:35','2013-06-25 06:13:35','',339,'http://localhost/wordpress/339-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(341,1,'2013-06-25 07:21:14','2013-06-25 07:21:14','test1','test1','','publish','closed','closed','','test1','','','2013-06-25 07:21:27','2013-06-25 07:21:27','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=341',0,'tribe_events','',0),(342,1,'2013-06-25 07:21:50','2013-06-25 07:21:50','test2','test2','','publish','closed','closed','','test2','','','2013-06-25 07:21:50','2013-06-25 07:21:50','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=342',0,'tribe_events','',0),(343,1,'2013-06-25 07:22:52','2013-06-25 07:22:52','test2','test2','','inherit','open','open','','342-autosave','','','2013-06-25 07:22:52','2013-06-25 07:22:52','',342,'http://localhost/wordpress/342-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(344,1,'2013-06-25 09:01:57','2013-06-25 09:01:57','','pics','','inherit','open','open','','pics','','','2013-06-25 09:01:57','2013-06-25 09:01:57','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/pics.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(345,1,'2013-06-25 10:04:22','2013-06-25 10:04:22','','pic2','','inherit','open','open','','pic2','','','2013-06-25 10:04:22','2013-06-25 10:04:22','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/pic2.jpg',3,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(346,1,'2013-06-25 10:04:23','2013-06-25 10:04:23','','pic3','','inherit','open','open','','pic3','','','2013-06-25 10:04:23','2013-06-25 10:04:23','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/pic3.jpg',2,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(347,1,'2013-06-25 10:04:24','2013-06-25 10:04:24','','pic4','','inherit','open','open','','pic4','','','2013-06-25 10:04:24','2013-06-25 10:04:24','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/pic4.jpg',4,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(348,1,'2013-06-25 10:49:18','2013-06-25 10:49:18',' ','','','publish','open','open','','348','','','2013-06-25 10:49:18','2013-06-25 10:49:18','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=348',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(349,1,'2013-06-25 11:23:33','2013-06-25 11:23:33','','Why Mount Carmel School?','','publish','open','open','','why-mount-carmel-school','','','2013-06-25 11:23:33','2013-06-25 11:23:33','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=349',0,'page','',0),(350,1,'2013-06-26 09:02:21','2013-06-26 09:02:21','','Calendar','','publish','open','open','','calendar','','','2013-06-27 09:52:40','2013-06-27 09:52:40','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=350',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(351,1,'2013-06-26 09:46:57','2013-06-26 09:46:57','','Gallery','','publish','open','open','','gallery','','','2013-06-27 09:52:40','2013-06-27 09:52:40','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=351',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(352,1,'2013-06-21 06:14:47','2013-06-21 06:14:47','<ul>\r\n	<li>All the students are expected to come to school in full uniform, clean and neatly dressed. No relaxation, whatsoever, in uniform will be allowed.</li>\r\n	<li>Students should be in school at least five minutes before the first bell at 7.45 a.m. in summer and 8.15 a.m. in winter. Punctuality is very necessary.</li>\r\n	<li>Students will not be allowed to leave the school premises during the school hours without the Principal’s / Vice Principal’s permission.</li>\r\n	<li>No leave of absence will be granted except on prior written application from parents/guardians. Leave of absence will be granted only in exceptional circumstances. What the exceptional circumstances are, will be determined by the school authorities. Defaulters will be fined.</li>\r\n	<li>No story books, comics, periodicals, pictures or newspapers except those allowed by the school shall be brought to the school nor circulated without the permission of the Principal/ Vice- Principal.</li>\r\n	<li>No jewellery is allowed in the school. Girls with pierced ears may wear thin silver wire earrings. Watches may be worn only by students of classes VII and above.</li>\r\n	<li>No borrowing or lending of money or exchanging of articles is allowed in the school.\r\nStudents will be required to make good any damages done to the school property.</li>\r\n	<li>Mobile phones are not allowed in the school. No student is allowed to bring any other electrical/electronic gadget to the school.</li>\r\n	<li>Students will be allowed to use the school telephone only in urgent cases and that too with the Principal\'s/Vice Principal’s permission. Visitors are not allowed to meet the students in school.</li>\r\n	<li>The school expects the students to be honest and sincere in all their ways. Polite behaviour and gentleness in speech and manner will be insisted upon at all times.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents should supply their children with a wholesome &amp; substantial lunch each day, so that they will not be compelled to patronize dispensers of unwholesome food, outside the school.</li>\r\n	<li>No tiffin will be accepted for any students during the school hours, for security reasons.</li>\r\n	<li>Pupils must attend games and other activities outside school hours when required to do so and participation in such circumstances will be deemed necessary by the school authorities.</li>\r\n	<li>No student (except those in classes XI &amp; XII) is allowed to bring any 2-wheeler to school.</li>\r\n	<li>No 4-wheeler is allowed in school.</li>\r\n</ul>','School Rules and Regulations','','inherit','open','open','','192-revision-4','','','2013-06-21 06:14:47','2013-06-21 06:14:47','',192,'http://localhost/wordpress/192-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(353,1,'2013-06-21 11:46:12','2013-06-21 11:46:12','<h1>Admissions</h1>\r\n\r\n<center><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/online-admission/\" target=_blank>\r\n<div class=\"div_link\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><b>Apply Online</b></div>\r\n</a></center>\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" />\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admissions to all the classes are ordinarily made in December and January for the academic year starting in April. However children are registered for all classes from November.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admissions are made on the basis of merit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students coming from other schools should produce: -\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The leaving/transfer certificate from the school last attended / bonafide certificate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The progress report of his/her academic performance and co-curricular activities in      that  school.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The original birth certificate &amp; a copy of the same.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>A calendar month’s notice in writing should be given by the parents before withdrawing a student from the school. Failure to do so will entail paying fees for the entire term.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students leaving school after December will pay fees for January, February and March also.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">All dues to the school should be paid before applying for transfer certificate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The transfer and other school certificates will be applied for in writing, one week in advance.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The refund of caution money will be made only at the end of the session, on due notice.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Principal can at any time in the interest of the school have a student removed, if in the Pricipal\'s sole discretion, the student or his/her parents/guardian fail to abide by the rules and regulations and in case there is lack of co-operation on the part of the parent in maintaining discipline of the school and his/her continued presence is deterimental to the interest of the other students.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #800000; font-size: 20px;\">Examination &amp; Promotion</span></h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Continuous &amp; Comprehensive Evaluation (C.C.E) introduced by the CBSE, Delhi, which is a system of School Based Assessment that covers all aspects of the student\'s development, is followed in the school. C.C.E covers both the scholastic and co-scholastic aspects of school education.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The school academic year has two terms, April to Sep. and Oct. to March. There will be a Summative assessment for classes VI to X at the end of each term. Besides these there will be two unit tests in each subject as a part of the two Formative assessments, in each term. However there will be no such summative assessments for classes Pre-Nursery to V and only two two evaluations (details would be given along with the syllabus) will be conducted for the students of class I to V. Progress cards will be issued to the students only at the end of the session.\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 100px;\">Assessments (classes VI to X)\r\nUnit tests : 20 marks\r\nOther Assessments, Project work etc. :30 marks\r\nSummative Assessements(classes VI to X) :100 marks</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Assessments/Unit Tests will neither be anticipated nor postponed. Any tampering with marks will be seriously dealt with. Students who are ill should not be sent to appear for Assessments/Unit Tests. Their results can be decided on the basis of their performance in class. However a medical certificate will have to be produced in such cases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students found using any unfair means during Assessments/Unit Tests will be marked zero in that subject. No re-test will be held for such students and they will not be eligible for any academic award or school appointment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Criteria for the award of a Scholar Badge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>VI-VIII : Grade A1 (Marks range 91-100) Eng, Hindi, Maths, S. Science, Gen. Science.\r\nIX: Grade A1 (Marks range 91-100) Eng, IInd Lang., Maths, S. Science, Gen. Science</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The final result will be decided according to the average marks obtained in two terms.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Results declared at the close of the year are final and will not be reconsidered.</li>\r\n</ul>','Admissions','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-47','','','2013-06-21 11:46:12','2013-06-21 11:46:12','',8,'http://localhost/wordpress/8-revision-47/',0,'revision','',0),(354,1,'2013-06-27 06:39:37','2013-06-27 06:39:37','&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"div_link\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><b>Apply Online</b></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" />\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admissions to all the classes are ordinarily made in December and January for the academic year starting in April. However children are registered for all classes from November.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admissions are made on the basis of merit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students coming from other schools should produce: -\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The leaving/transfer certificate from the school last attended / bonafide certificate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The progress report of his/her academic performance and co-curricular activities in      that  school.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li type=\"circle\">The original birth certificate &